We use 3 api's to check the location. Unfortunately we have seen a couple cases where the IP shows up different on the different API's. Sometimes this is due to the API being incorrect and sometimes the service provider of that IP is doing some weird things behind the scenes (I have seen an IP where various API's showed 3 or 4 different locations that weren't even that close together which probably means that service provider is doing something and saying the IP is in the location they're presenting it as even if it isn't.

As suggested by someone else above, you can check the API's we use to see what it identifies your IP as if you're wanting to make sure it is recognized properly. If you have suggestions for a better API, we're open to suggestions and will look into any API's people think would be better. We do look into this on our own as well.
